501.definition: [ἀντλέω] from ἄντλος (the hold of a ship); to bale up (properly, bilge water), i.e. dip water (with a bucket, pitcher, etc.)

503.definition: [ἀντοφθαλμέω] from a compound of {{G473}} and {{G3788}}; to face

504.definition: [ἄνυδρος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G5204}}; waterless, i.e. dry

505.definition: [ἀνυπόκριτος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{G5271}}; undissembled, i.e. sincere

506.definition: [ἀνυπότακτος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{G5293}}; unsubdued, i.e. insubordinate (in fact or temper)

507.definition: [ἄνω] adverb from {{G473}}; upward or on the top

508.definition: [ἀνώγεον] from {{G507}} and {{G1093}}; above the ground, i.e. (properly) the second floor of a building; used for a dome or a balcony on the upper story

509.definition: [ἄνωθεν] from {{G507}}; from above; by analogy, from the first; by implication, anew

511.definition: [ἀνώτερος] comparative degree of {{G507}}; upper, i.e. (neuter as adverb) to a more conspicuous place, in a former part of the book

512.definition: [ἀνωφελής] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and the base of {{G5624}}; useless or (neuter) inutility

513.definition: [ἀξίνη] probably from ἄγνυμι (to break; compare {{G4486}}); an axe

514.definition: [ἄξιος] probably from {{G71}}; deserving, comparable or suitable (as if drawing praise)

515.definition: [ἀξιόω] from {{G514}}; to deem entitled or fit

517.definition: [ἀόρατος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G3707}}; invisible

518.definition: [ἀπαγγέλλω] from {{G575}} and the base of {{G32}}; to announce

519.definition: [ἀπάγχομαι] from {{G575}} and ἄγχω (to choke; akin to the base of {{G43}}); to strangle oneself off (i.e. to death)

520.definition: [ἀπάγω] from {{G575}} and {{G71}}; to take off (in various senses)

521.definition: [ἀπαίδευτος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{G3811}}; uninstructed, i.e. (figuratively) stupid

522.definition: [ἀπαίρω] from {{G575}} and {{G142}}; to lift off, i.e. remove

524.definition: [ἀπαλγέω] from {{G575}} and ἀλγέω (to smart); to grieve out, i.e. become apathetic

525.definition: [ἀπαλλάσσω] from {{G575}} and {{G236}}; to change away, i.e. release, (reflexively) remove

526.definition: [ἀπαλλοτριόω] from {{G575}} and a derivative of {{G245}}; to estrange away, i.e. (passively and figuratively) to be non-participant

528.definition: [ἀπαντάω] from {{G575}} and a derivative of {{G473}}; to meet away, i.e. encounter

530.definition: [ἅπαξ] probably from {{G537}}; one (or a single) time (numerically or conclusively)

531.definition: [ἀπαράβατος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{G3845}}; not passing away, i.e. untransferable (perpetual)

532.definition: [ἀπαρασκεύαστος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{G3903}}; unready

533.definition: [ἀπαρνέομαι] from {{G575}} and {{G720}}; to deny utterly, i.e. disown, abstain

534.definition: [ἀπάρτι] from {{G575}} and {{G737}}; from now, i.e. henceforth (already)

536.definition: [ἀπαρχή] from a compound of {{G575}} and {{G756}}; a beginning of sacrifice, i.e. the (Jewish) first-fruit (figuratively)

537.definition: [ἅπας] from {{G1}} (as a particle of union) and {{G3956}}; absolutely all or (singular) every one

538.definition: [ἀπατάω] of uncertain derivation; to cheat, i.e. delude

540.definition: [ἀπάτωρ] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G3962}}; fatherless, i.e. of unrecorded paternity

541.definition: [ἀπαύγασμα] from a compound of {{G575}} and {{G826}}; an off-flash, i.e. effulgence

542.definition: [ἀπείδω] from {{G575}} and the same as {{G1492}}; to see fully

545.definition: [ἀπειθής] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G3982}}; unpersuadable, i.e. contumacious

546.definition: [ἀπειλέω] of uncertain derivation; to menace; by implication, to forbid

548.definition: [ἄπειμι] from {{G575}} and {{G1510}}; to be away Compare {{G549}}.

549.definition: [ἄπειμι] from {{G575}} and εἶμι (to go); to go away Compare {{G548}}.

550.definition: [ἀπειπόμην] reflexive past of a compound of {{G575}} and {{G2036}}; to say off for oneself, i.e. disown

551.definition: [ἀπείραστος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{G3987}}; untried, i.e. not temptable

552.definition: [ἄπειρος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G3984}}; inexperienced, i.e. ignorant

554.definition: [ἀπεκδύομαι] middle voice from {{G575}} and {{G1562}}; to divest wholly oneself, or (for oneself) despoil

557.definition: [ἀπελεγμός] from a compound of {{G575}} and {{G1651}}; refutation, i.e. (by implication) contempt

558.definition: [ἀπελεύθερος] from {{G575}} and {{G1658}}; one freed away, i.e. a freedman

559.definition: [Ἀπελλῆς] of Latin origin; Apelles, a Christian

560.definition: [ἀπελπίζω] from {{G575}} and {{G1679}}; to hope out, i.e. fully expect

561.definition: [ἀπέναντι] from {{G575}} and {{G1725}}; from in front, i.e. opposite, before or against

562.definition: [ἀπέραντος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a secondary derivative of {{G4008}}; unfinished, i.e. (by implication) interminable

563.definition: [ἀπερισπάστως] adverb from a compound of {{G1}} (as a negative participle) and a presumed derivative of {{G4049}}; undistractedly, i.e. free from (domestic) solicitude

564.definition: [ἀπερίτμητος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{G4059}}; uncircumcised (figuratively)

565.definition: [ἀπέρχομαι] from {{G575}} and {{G2064}}; to go off (i.e. depart), aside (i.e. apart) or behind (i.e. follow), literally or figuratively

566.definition: [ἀπέχει] third person singular present indicative active of {{G568}} used impersonally; it is sufficient

567.definition: [ἀπέχομαι] middle voice (reflexively) of {{G568}}; to hold oneself off, i.e. refrain

568.definition: [ἀπέχω] from {{G575}} and {{G2192}}; (actively) to have out, i.e. receive in full; (intransitively) to keep (oneself) away, i.e. be distant (literally or figuratively)

569.definition: [ἀπιστέω] from {{G571}}; to be unbelieving, i.e. (transitively) disbelieve, or (by implication) disobey

570.definition: [ἀπιστία] from {{G571}}; faithlessness, i.e. (negatively) disbelief (lack of Christian faith), or (positively) unfaithfulness (disobedience)

571.definition: [ἄπιστος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G4103}}; (actively) disbelieving, i.e. without Christian faith (specially, a heathen); (passively) untrustworthy (person), or incredible (thing)

572.definition: [ἁπλότης] from {{G573}}; singleness, i.e. (subjectively) sincerity (without dissimulation or self-seeking), or (objectively) generosity (copious bestowal)

573.definition: [ἁπλοῦς] probably from {{G1}} (as a particle of union) and the base of {{G4120}}; properly, folded together, i.e. single (figuratively, clear)

574.definition: [ἁπλῶς] adverb from {{G573}} (in the objective sense of {{G572}}); bountifully;

575.definition: [ἀπό] a primary particle; "off," i.e. away (from something near), in various senses (of place, time, or relation; literal or figurative) In composition (as a prefix) it usually denotes separation, departure, cessation, completion, reversal, etc.

576.definition: [ἀποβαίνω] from {{G575}} and the base of {{G939}}; literally, to disembark; figuratively, to eventuate

577.definition: [ἀποβάλλω] from {{G575}} and {{G906}}; to throw off; figuratively, to lose

578.definition: [ἀποβλέπω] from {{G575}} and {{G991}}; to look away from everything else, i.e. (figuratively) intently regard

579.definition: [ἀπόβλητος] from {{G577}}; cast off, i.e. (figuratively) such as to be rejected

581.definition: [ἀπογενόμενος] past participle of a compound of {{G575}} and {{G1096}}; absent, i.e. deceased (figuratively, renounced)

582.definition: [ἀπογραφή] from {{G583}}; an enrollment; by implication, an assessment

583.definition: [ἀπογράφω] from {{G575}} and {{G1125}}; to write off (a copy or list), i.e. enrol

584.definition: [ἀποδείκνυμι] from {{G575}} and {{G1166}}; to show off, i.e. exhibit; figuratively, to demonstrate, i.e. accredit

586.definition: [ἀποδεκατόω] from {{G575}} and {{G1183}}; to tithe (as debtor or creditor)

588.definition: [ἀποδέχομαι] from {{G575}} and {{G1209}}; to take fully, i.e. welcome (persons), approve (things)

589.definition: [ἀποδημέω] from {{G590}}; to go abroad, i.e. visit a foreign land

590.definition: [ἀπόδημος] from {{G575}} and {{G1218}}; absent from one's own people, i.e. a foreign traveller

591.definition: [ἀποδίδωμι] from {{G575}} and {{G1325}}; to give away, i.e. up, over, back, etc. (in various applications)

592.definition: [ἀποδιορίζω] from {{G575}} and a compound of {{G1223}} and {{G3724}}; to disjoin (by a boundary, figuratively, a party)

593.definition: [ἀποδοκιμάζω] from {{G575}} and {{G1381}}; to disapprove, i.e. (by implication) to repudiate

595.definition: [ἀπόθεσις] from {{G659}}; a laying aside (literally or figuratively)

598.definition: [ἀποθλίβω] from {{G575}} and {{G2346}}; to crowd (from every side)

599.definition: [ἀποθνήσκω] from {{G575}} and {{G2348}}; to die off (literally or figuratively)

600.definition: [ἀποκαθίστημι] from {{G575}} and {{G2525}}; to reconstitute (in health, home or organization)
